Message.Title: Biggest Tech Stock Boom of Our Lifetimes Now Beginning!
Message.Msg: Big Data Analytics is the biggest buzz on Wall Street today with Big Data IPOs Tableau Software (DATA) and Splunk (SPLK) now up 82% and 176% from their IPO prices respectively, and now both trading with price/sales ratios of 22! The extremely valuable insight that companies will gain by using Big Data Analytics solutions - will revolutionize many industries - with one of the biggest being cable TV! Shockingly, the Big Data market share leader in the cable TV industry is already public today with EPS up 175% last quarter, yet it's only trading with an enterprise value of 0.69X revenue! The company is Concurrent (CCUR) and it closed yesterday at $7.57. CCUR has a huge cash position, no debt, and an enterprise value of $43.9 million or just 0.69X its trailing revenues of $63.23 million vs. DATA and SPLK trading for 22X sales. CCUR has operating cash flow of $7.13 million, giving it an extremely low enterprise value/cash flow ratio of 6 vs. DATA and SPLK being valued at 224X and 77X cash flow, respectively! If CCUR is only able to reach a very conservative enterprise value/revenue ratio of 2, it will rise by 125% to $17 per share, where CCUR will also be worth a very conservative 18X cash flow! The majority of North America's largest cable TV operators including Time Warner Cable, Cox, Charter, Rogers, and Bright House, are already using CCUR's Big Data Analytics solutions! CCUR already tracks the viewing behavior of 35 million pay-TV subscribers across all screens, platforms, and networks - in real time - with CCUR processing an enormous 15 billion media transactions so far! Only CCUR's Big Data platform is able to process the media data of linear TV, video on demand (VOD), IP-based CDNs, Network DVR, and more - with CCUR displaying results on visually rich interactive dashboards, accessible to its clients on all connected devices!
